LAFIA – Ibrahim Balarabe Abdullahi, the Speaker, Nasarawa State House of Assembly, on Monday urged Nigerians to remain hopeful and steadfast as there is hope for a better nation. The Speaker stated this in Lafia while speaking with newsmen on Nigeria at 59 and Nasarawa State at 23. He called on Nigerians to continue to pray and support President Muhammadu Buhari and other leaders to succeed in the task ahead of them. He said: “There is no doubt that President Muhammadu Buhari is a man of integrity who has the passion of the nation at heart. “And he is doing his possible best for a prosperous Nigeria and all we need is to pray and support him so that we will enjoy more dividends of democracy,” he said. The Speaker, who emphasised that challenges are part of human existence and Nigeria cannot be exception, noted that the country’s challenges can be overcome. He added that efforts of the country’s heroes past shall never go in vain. Balarabe urged all Nigerians to renew their faith and commitments for a better nation. On Nasarawa at 23, the Speaker felicitated with the people of the state and commended the efforts of the past governors in building the state while urging all to support Gov. Abdullahi Sule’s administration to succeed. “We in Nasarawa as a state, 23 years has gone by and no doubt we are growing gradually, we thank God for giving us Governor Abdullahi Sule who have the passion and interest of the state at heart.”